(comics)|Armadillo]], [[Equinox (comics)|Equinox]], [[List of Marvel Comics characters: H#Hypno-Hustler|Hypno-Hustler]], [[Big Wheel (comics)|Jackson Weele]], and [[Man-Bull]].<ref>''Spider-Man Unlimited'' #13</ref>\n\nIn ''[[Civil War (comic book)|Civil War]]: Battle Damage Report'', it is revealed that Chip and [[Lectronn]] engaged in a three hour fight over New York that ended in a stalemate.<ref>''Civil War: Battle Damage Report'' #1</ref>\n\nSchizoid Man was among several super-powered criminals housed in an unnamed ill-equipped prison in the aftermath of the ''[[Avengers Vs. X-Men]]'' storyline. [[Rogue (comics)|Rogue]] and [[Mimic (comics)|Mimic]] had to fight them off during a prison riot where Schizoid Man was trying to get control of himself.<ref>''X-Men Legacy'' #275.</ref>\n\n==Powers and abilities==\nSchizoid Man possesses the power of building and animating solid constructs with his mind.\n\n==Other versions==\n===Ultimate Marvel===\nThe [[Ultimate Marvel]] version of Schizoid Man is a mutate created by modifying a (presumably French) man using a cell sample from [[Jamie Madrox|Multiple Man]]. This grants him similar self-replication powers. He is used to control a riot at least once, and eventually joins the [[Liberators (Marvel Comics)|Liberators]].<ref>''Ultimates'' Vol. 2 #9</ref> His team, leading a large army, invades and conquers the United States, leading to mass civilian deaths.<ref>''Ultimates'' Vol. 2 #10</ref> He is defeated by [[Captain America]] who after being released from his cell by the [[Wasp (comics)|Wasp]], defeats all of his bodies which are later said to be \"scattered all over the [[Triskelion (comics)|Triskelion]].\"<ref>''Ultimates'' Vol. 2 #11</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://marvel.wikia.com/Chip_Martin_%28Earth-616%29 Schizoid Man] at Marvel Wiki\n* [http://marvel.wikia.com/James_Madrox_%28Schizoid_Man%29_%28Earth-1610%29 Schizoid Man (Earth-1610)] at Marvel Wiki\n* {{Marvunapp|http://ww